<DOC><DOCNO> AP890616-0169 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-16-89 2249EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-HeavyChoice     06-16 0238</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Heavy Choice,0243</SECOND><HEAD>Judge: Lose Weight or Go to Jail</HEAD><DATELINE>JIM THORPE, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A 311{-pound man who hasn't made childsupport payments for more than a year because he's too overweight towork is under court order to lose 50 pounds or go to jail.   Charles Petro has gained 85 pounds in the year since his doctortold the Carbon County Court that obesity was making his patient'sback condition worse.   Common Pleas Court President Judge John P. Lavelle found Petro incontempt of court on June 9 because Petro had gained the weight inthe year since he first went before the judge for the same reason.   ``I call it my `Oprah Winfrey sentence,''' Lavelle said Thursday.``It's designed to make him lose weight for the benefit of hischildren, while Oprah lost weight for the benefit of her job andfuture security.''   Lavelle set Sept. 9 as the deadline for Petro to shed 50 poundsor go to jail for 90 days. To verify Petro's weight, the judge senthim to a nearby medical center where he was weighed.   ``I said to him, `No sacrifice should be too much for a man whohas a duty to support his children,'' Lavelle said. ``The only waythis man will ever get back to being a productive worker is if heloses weight.''   Petro, who has two children, could not be reached Friday forcomment.</TEXT></DOC>